title: Works for what I need it for but has issues
comment: This emulator badly needs save states!   Ran into a bug (feature?) where if you reset the emu using the reset command from the menu prompt, it can, and will, completely delete your save file and progress on the game that is running once reset. As you might imagine is a big issue on an emulator that doesn't have save states.  Seeing as this is the only Wonderswan emulator I can find for Android, and seeing as the quality is pretty good (minimal lag skips depending on what my phone is doing in the background, great sound quality, relatively responsive on screen touch controls), I don't have any other choice but to use it.   If I may suggest a few improvements that you may have already heard before: -Save states: Given the alpha nature of this app, this is a given when in game stuff doesn't work. -Allow the option to have the touch screen controls enabled on start-up, and remember the preference. -Allow orientation flip either by use of accelerometer or option in the menus. My headphone jack is in a troublesome position when I play, and I'd appreciate the ability to flip the screen 180 deg.  Thanks for providing an otherwise quality niche emulator! -On an HTC One X, AT&T
